m curious if it’s meant to report the dynamic-access call sites executed during the tests. There’s a lot to unpack here, so I’ll need to consider how instrumentation interacts with dynamic access and what that means for test execution. It’s definitely intriguing!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Thinking about code cleanup**\\n\\nI’m considering whether it’s okay to remove an unused file named Keycloak_client from the ReflectionsTest directory. I think it could help avoid scaffold-only clutter. It seems like using bash for file operations is encouraged, so I should do that. But I’m a bit hesitant about whether the build expects anything. However, I feel confident that deleting the placeholder is a good move. Overall, I think I’ll go ahead and proceed with the rm command.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_G5mD8AyhefyyALU3Kkj6dpV8|fc_044bd184f90432930169f69293e7e8819db70d4ed5039a2078", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.keycloak/keycloak-client-common-synced/26.0.9/src/test/java/org_keycloak/keycloak_client_common_synced/ReflectionsTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_keycloak.keycloak_client_common_synced;\n\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertFalse;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNotNull;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertSame;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Constructor;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Set;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.keycloak.common.util.reflections.Reflections;\n\npublic class ReflectionsTest {\n    @Test\n    public void classForNameUsesContextFallbackAndDefaultLoaders() throws Exception {\n        ClassLoader originalClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        String subjectName = ClassForNameSubject.class.getName();\n\n        try {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(ReflectionsTest.class.getClassLoader());\n            assertSame(ClassForNameSubject.class, Reflections.classForName(subjectName));\n\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(null);\n            assertSame(ClassForNameSubject.class, Reflections.classForName(subjectName));\n\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(new BlockingClassLoader());\n            assertSame(ClassForNameSubject.class,\n                    Reflections.classForName(subjectName, ReflectionsTest.class.getClassLoader()));\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void findsMembersAcrossClassHierarchyAndUsesThem() throws Exception {\n        ChildSubject subject = new ChildSubject();\n\n        Set<Field> fields = Reflections.getAllDeclaredFields(ChildSubject.class);\n        assertTrue(containsField(fields, \"childField\"));\n        assertTrue(containsField(fields, \"parentField\"));\n\n        Field parentField = Reflections.findDeclaredField(ChildSubject.class, \"parentField\");\n        assertNotNull(parentField);\n        Reflections.setAccessible(parentField);\n        assertEquals(\"parent\", Reflections.getFieldValue(parentField, subject, String.class));\n\n        assertTrue(Reflections.methodExists(ChildSubject.class, \"parentGreeting\"));\n        assertFalse(Reflections.methodExists(ChildSubject.class, \"missingMethod\"));\n\n        Set<Method> methods = Reflections.getAllDeclaredMethods(ChildSubject.class);\n        assertTrue(containsMethod(methods, \"childGreeting\"));\n        assertTrue(containsMethod(methods, \"parentGreeting\"));\n\n        Method parentGreeting = Reflections.findDeclaredMethod(ChildSubject.class, \"parentGreeting\", String.class);\n        assertNotNull(parentGreeting);\n        assertEquals(\"hello parent\", Reflections.invokeMethod(true, parentGreeting, String.class, subject, \"hello\"));\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void findsDeclaredConstructors() {\n        Constructor<?> stringConstructor = Reflections.findDeclaredConstructor(ConstructorSubject.class, String.class);\n        assertNotNull(stringConstructor);\n\n        Set<Constructor<?>> constructors = Reflections.getAllDeclaredConstructors(ConstructorSubject.class);\n        assertTrue(constructors.contains(stringConstructor));\n        assertTrue(constructors.size() >= 2);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void identifiesNonPrivateFinalMethod() {\n        Object finalMethodOrType = Reflections.getNonPrivateFinalMethodOrType(FinalMethodSubject.class);\n        assertTrue(finalMethodOrType instanceof Method);\n        assertEquals(\"finalMethod\", Method.class.cast(finalMethodOrType).getName());\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void resolvesRawListTypeFromFieldValue() throws Exception {\n        Field rawListField = Reflections.findDeclaredField(RawListHolder.class, \"values\");\n        assertNotNull(rawListField);\n        Reflections.setAccessible(rawListField);\n\n        assertSame(String.class, Reflections.resolveListType(rawListField, new RawListHolder()));\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"deprecation\")\n    public void createsNewInstancesByClassName() throws Exception {\n        NewInstanceSubject subject = Reflections.newInstance(NewInstanceSubject.class);\n\n        assertTrue(subject.created);\n    }\n\n    private static boolean containsField(Set<Field> fields, String name) {\n        for (Field field : fields) {\n            if (field.getName().equals(name)) {\n                return true;\n            }\n        }\n        return false;\n    }\n\n    private static boolean containsMethod(Set<Method> methods, String name) {\n        for (Method method : methods) {\n            if (method.getName().equals(name)) {\n                return true;\n            }\n        }\n        return false;\n    }\n\n    private static final class BlockingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        BlockingClassLoader() {\n            super(null);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class ParentSubject {\n        private final String parentField = \"parent\";\n\n        private String parentGreeting(String prefix) {\n            return prefix + \" \" + parentField;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class ChildSubject extends ParentSubject {\n        private final String childField = \"child\";\n\n        public String childGreeting() {\n            return childField;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class ConstructorSubject {\n        public ConstructorSubject() {\n        }\n\n        public ConstructorSubject(String value) {\n            assertNotNull(value);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class FinalMethodSubject {\n        public final String finalMethod() {\n            return \"final\";\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class RawListHolder {\n        @SuppressWarnings(\"rawtypes\")\n        private final List values = new ArrayList<String>();\n\n        RawListHolder() {\n            values.add(\"item\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class NewInstanceSubject {\n        private final boolean created;\n\n        public NewInstanceSubject() {\n            this.created = true;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class ClassForNameSubject {\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3826, "output": 3367, "cacheRead": 23040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30233, "cost": {"input": 0, "output